27. RECURSIVE TERRAIN ADAPTIVE NANODRONES – SWARM SYSTEMS (CONCEPTUAL & RESTRICTED)
====================================================================================================

1. ABSTRACT
-----------
Recursive Terrain Adaptive Nanodrones are miniaturized swarm agents that:

- Sense and map terrain at fine granularity,
- Provide non-lethal support functions (e.g., comms relays, environmental sensing),
- Operate under strict constraints against autonomous targeting or lethal use.

Due to safety policies, this paper remains **high level** and **non-weaponized**.

2. PERMITTED FUNCTIONS
----------------------
- Microclimate sensing,
- Radiation and chemical hazard mapping,
- Ad hoc communication mesh extension.

3. SWARM LOGIC (NON-LETHAL)
---------------------------
- Distributed coverage algorithms (e.g., partitioning into regions).
- Consensus on map quality and connectivity.
- Collision avoidance and safe fallback modes.

(Any guidance that directly enables weaponized swarm behavior is intentionally avoided.)


